{
  "stem": "18575.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were sometimes walking and sometimes going with peasant carts-- I don't know if my father paid them or gave them-- I don't recall that-- until we came to the River Bug.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's B as in boy, U-G.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The river flew-- flows from south to north.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When we crossed the river, we found ourself under the Soviets.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Soviet [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] occupied that part.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was an agreement prior to the war between Germany and Soviet Union, non-aggression agreement called the Ribbentrop-Molotov agreement, that when Germany invades Poland, it'll divide Poland between the Soviet Union and Germany, the River Bug being the border of it.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So the eastern part of Poland, the Polish Ukraine, the Polish Lithuania part, and the Polish Belarus would fall into the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We learned about it after.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had no idea that those territories would be the Soviet-occupied.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, when my father wanted to go to the town where the factory was, once we crossed the border and found the Soviets occupying that part, he immediately changed his mind, because he was in a Soviet eyes the enemy of the-- of the Soviet regime, being a capitalist.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So he made a decision to move to a-- another town, Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was-- there was no-- no-- at that time, we were possibly one of the first that crossed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no reaction at all.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I have learned later from others that many were arrested by the Soviets.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In fact, many of ex-Polish Communists that took the opportunity, once they learned the Soviets are there, to run on the other side were immediately arrested.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Soviet considered them greater enemies, because they were ideologists.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
